00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:46,990
(When My Love Blooms)

4
00:04:22,090 --> 00:04:24,960
I don't think superstitions are always bad.

5
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:28,090
They're not, but it doesn't taste nice.

6
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:31,030
I'm sick of beans and tofu.

7
00:04:31,570 --> 00:04:33,230
I apologize.

8
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:36,040
Where are all the people who wept when I went in?

9
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:38,200
Why are you alone?

10
00:04:38,510 --> 00:04:42,010
They're all in the unexpected executive meeting.

11
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:45,450
They wouldn't be happy to see me after four years.

12
00:04:45,450 --> 00:04:47,120
I'm not the Olympic Games.

13
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:50,120
You must really be careful. The atmosphere is really bad.

14
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,850
All your people were fired,

15
00:04:51,850 --> 00:04:53,590
and the company's always frigid.

16
00:04:53,590 --> 00:04:55,390
Frigid?

17
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:58,120
It suddenly turned freezing cold.

18
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,330
It'll get even worse.

19
00:05:00,330 --> 00:05:02,760
Why? Is something wrong again?

20
00:05:03,770 --> 00:05:06,260
A typhoon's moving in.

21
00:05:08,770 --> 00:05:11,970
Why come all the way here when the weather's bad?

22
00:05:11,970 --> 00:05:13,610
I don't like chain supermarkets.

23
00:05:13,610 --> 00:05:15,280
Why is that?

24
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:16,680
Their goods are much cheaper.

25
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:19,680
That's why I hate them. That's why I got fired.

26
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:22,120
You even have a university degree.

27
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,750
Why work at a supermarket?

28
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:26,620
- Because I have a record. - A record?

29
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,490
- What kind? - The criminal kind.

30
00:05:28,490 --> 00:05:30,420
It's quite something.

31
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:38,270
Ma'am. You should expect a special visitor.

32
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:40,640
What? A ghost?

33
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:42,240
Not a ghost. A special visitor.

34
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:44,410
A morning spider means a special visitor.

35
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:45,770
Evening spiders mean robbers.

36
00:05:45,770 --> 00:05:48,110
Why did that thing come out here...

37
00:05:48,110 --> 00:05:51,210
