Without even leaving a name

90
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:15,200
We agreed to fight forever

91
00:11:56,210 --> 00:11:59,210
- Is it any fun? - It's so much fun.

92
00:11:59,210 --> 00:12:01,750
I was so surprised.

93
00:12:02,920 --> 00:12:05,380
Hey. It's what you like.

94
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,320
You go ahead.

95
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:10,630
Next up is the keynote speech from Han Jae Hyun,

96
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:12,290
who majors in law.

97
00:12:12,290 --> 00:12:17,930
(Stop making us sad.)

98
00:12:17,930 --> 00:12:19,630
(The 13th Anniversary of Gwangju Uprising)

99
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:25,040
(Memorial for Democratic Martyrs and Opening Ceremony)

100
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:27,040
Hello, fellow students!

101
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:29,910
I'm Han Jae Hyun, class of 1995, studying law.

102
00:12:30,110 --> 00:12:31,880
I fight for democracy...

103
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,510
and labour laws,

104
00:12:33,510 --> 00:12:35,810
and greet you all today!

105
00:12:38,820 --> 00:12:42,990
(Memorial for Democratic Martyrs and Opening Ceremony)

106
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:46,330
Today, to fight for a better tomorrow,

107
00:12:46,330 --> 00:12:48,360
we take to the streets again.

108
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:50,700
Times have changed,

109
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:53,100
and some might ask why we still do this.

110
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:54,970
But listen!

111
00:12:54,970 --> 00:12:58,870
There are still places and people who need us!

112
00:12:58,870 --> 00:13:00,640
In Gwangju in 1980,

113
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:03,140
people fought for democracy...

114
00:13:03,140 --> 00:13:06,280
and were cut down and shot by soldiers.

115
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:08,180
Without an investigation into...

116
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:09,780
who gave the order,

117
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:13,050
they were written off as communists and violent mobs.

118
00:13:13,050 --> 00:13:14,720
In the name of redevelopment,

119
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:18,390
people are thrown out of homes they lived in for 30 years.

120
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:21,960
Under the excuse that they must prepare for a difficult future,

121
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:25,960
husbands and fathers are being let off with a short goodbye.

122
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:29,500
Our society swings too much to the right.

123
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:32,640
I'm not asking for the minimum respect and consideration.

124
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:36,970
I'm talking about the desperation of survival!

125
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:46,050
I found him. Han Jae Hyun.

126
