I'm trying to do just that.

158
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:30,140
- What are you... - It's my life's blood.

159
00:17:36,980 --> 00:17:38,680
Lady!

160
00:17:41,290 --> 00:17:43,650
I apologize. There was a weird lady.

161
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,620
What's that?

162
00:17:45,890 --> 00:17:47,360
She took the bottle of water...

163
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:48,960
but left this behind.

164
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:50,770
That's a man's handkerchief.

165
00:17:50,770 --> 00:17:52,770
She didn't look like the type to care.

166
00:17:52,770 --> 00:17:53,930
You know women...

167
00:17:53,930 --> 00:17:56,900
who don't mind wearing their husband's shorts or socks.

168
00:17:57,170 --> 00:17:59,270
- Jun Woo. - Yes?

169
00:17:59,270 --> 00:18:01,640
- Let's go to the company. - Okay.

170
00:18:01,740 --> 00:18:04,580
What? You won't go home?

171
00:18:04,580 --> 00:18:06,480
I must see the chairman first.

172
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:10,420
Dismissal is death! Cancel the dismissal!

173
00:18:10,420 --> 00:18:12,790
- Cancel! Cancel! - Cancel! Cancel!

174
00:18:12,790 --> 00:18:14,760
Mayflies only live for one day.

175
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,960
- Have some water. - We last two years.

176
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:18,760
That's how long our contracts last.

177
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:21,860
Anyone who works for over two years becomes a regular employee.

178
00:18:21,860 --> 00:18:23,730
So the company fires us after two years.

179
00:18:23,730 --> 00:18:25,130
We cry and beg...

180
00:18:25,130 --> 00:18:27,840
and fight, but we keep getting fired.

181
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:29,940
That's how we spend those two years.

182
00:18:29,940 --> 00:18:31,310
In fear.

183
